        %h2.section-heading.margin-bottomgap0.med-blue
          Phase 2
        %hr.section-heading-spacer
        %p.clear-left
          Create Working Prototype
        %p.clear-left.section-body-text
          With a clear understanding of the primary user scenario, I went straight to creating a rapid prototype with AngularJS and Middleman to further define page interactions and create HTML/CSS skeleton for the dev team. Skipping a static mockup was possible because we had clearly scoped all the interactions in the prior phase. This allowed me to show how the page would flow in addition to giving us the ability create design patterns for reuse throughout the project.
        %p.clear-left.section-body-text
          We defined a select group from our call center team and asked them to use the system. The team's interactions were recorded and reviewed in a seperate session with the stakeholders and lead developer. This step showed gaps in the system's call handling proceedure, where the consumer's location wasn't being captured at the time of the call. We adjusted the call system form and retested.
